com.appglu - package com.appglu
The main package of AppGlu's Java Client SDK.
Contain interfaces to describe all available operations and APIs as well as model objects to be used by these operations.
com.appglu.android - package com.appglu.android
The main package of AppGlu's Android SDK.
Contains the SDK's main class AppGlu and some utility classes to provide asynchronous execution using AsyncTask.
com.appglu.android.analytics - package com.appglu.android.analytics
Contains the Analytics API implementation for Android.
This includes a service, a SQLite repository and the AnalyticsDispatcher abstraction and implementation.
com.appglu.android.analytics.activity - package com.appglu.android.analytics.activity
Contains classes to be used as a base for your Android activities if you are using the Analytics API.
com.appglu.android.cache - package com.appglu.android.cache
Contains the CacheManager interface and it's implementations.
A CacheManager is used for storing and caching files while using the StorageApi.
com.appglu.android.log - package com.appglu.android.log
Contains classes that wrap the Android Log class to provide more sophisticated functionality like log levels and filtering.
com.appglu.android.storage - package com.appglu.android.storage
Contains the Storage API implementation for Android.
The Storage API has methods to download and cache files from AppGlu server.
com.appglu.android.sync - package com.appglu.android.sync
Contains the Sync API implementation for Android.
The Sync API is used to synchronize the data in your local SQLite tables with the AppGlu server.
com.appglu.android.util - package com.appglu.android.util
Utility classes.

UserOperations - Interface in com.appglu
UserOperations has methods to login / logout and sign up new mobile app users.
UserOperations depends on a implementation of UserSessionPersistence to keep track of the current logged in User.
UserSessionPersistence - Interface in com.appglu
Strategy for keeping track of the authenticated mobile application User.
When UserOperations.signup(User) or UserOperations.login(String, String) are called the User will be saved using UserSessionPersistence.saveAuthenticatedUser(User).
When UserOperations.logout() is called then the User will be removed using UserSessionPersistence.logout().
